82 bool ExplicitlyConfiguredSpatialLayers() const;

96 //
97 // Input:

103 size_t SteadyStateSize(int sid, int tid);

152 // Used for flexible mode.
153 bool is_flexible_mode_;
154 struct RefFrameBuffer {
155 RefFrameBuffer(size_t pic_num,
156 size_t spatial_layer_id,
157 size_t temporal_layer_id)
158 : pic_num(pic_num),
159 spatial_layer_id(spatial_layer_id),
160 temporal_layer_id(temporal_layer_id) {}
161 RefFrameBuffer() {}
162
163 bool operator==(const RefFrameBuffer& o) {
164 return pic_num == o.pic_num && spatial_layer_id == o.spatial_layer_id &&
165 temporal_layer_id == o.temporal_layer_id;
166 }
167
168 size_t pic_num = 0;
169 size_t spatial_layer_id = 0;
170 size_t temporal_layer_id = 0;
171 };
172 std::map<size_t, RefFrameBuffer> ref_buf_;
173 std::vector<ScalableVideoController::LayerFrameConfig> layer_frames_;
174
175 // Variable frame-rate related fields and methods.
176 const struct VariableFramerateExperiment {
177 bool enabled;
178 // Framerate is limited to this value in steady state.
179 float framerate_limit;
180 // This qp or below is considered a steady state.
181 int steady_state_qp;
182 // Frames of at least this percentage below ideal for configured bitrate are
183 // considered in a steady state.
184 int steady_state_undershoot_percentage;
185 // Number of consecutive frames with good QP and size required to detect
186 // the steady state.
187 int frames_before_steady_state;
188 } variable_framerate_experiment_;
189 static VariableFramerateExperiment ParseVariableFramerateConfig(
190 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials);
191 FramerateController variable_framerate_controller_;
192
193 const struct QualityScalerExperiment {
194 int low_qp;
195 int high_qp;
196 bool enabled;
197 } quality_scaler_experiment_;
198 static QualityScalerExperiment ParseQualityScalerConfig(
199 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials);
200 const bool external_ref_ctrl_;
201
202 // Flags that can affect speed vs quality tradeoff, and are configureable per
203 // resolution ranges.
204 struct PerformanceFlags {
205 // If false, a lookup will be made in |settings_by_resolution| base on the
206 // highest currently active resolution, and the overall speed then set to
207 // to the |base_layer_speed| matching that entry.
208 // If true, each active resolution will have it's speed and deblock_mode set
209 // based on it resolution, and the high layer speed configured for non
210 // base temporal layer frames.
211 bool use_per_layer_speed = false;
212
213 struct ParameterSet {
214 int base_layer_speed = -1; // Speed setting for TL0.
215 int high_layer_speed = -1; // Speed setting for TL1-TL3.
216 // 0 = deblock all temporal layers (TL)
217 // 1 = disable deblock for top-most TL
218 // 2 = disable deblock for all TLs
219 int deblock_mode = 0;
220 };
221 // Map from min pixel count to settings for that resolution and above.
222 // E.g. if you want some settings A if below wvga (640x360) and some other
223 // setting B at wvga and above, you'd use map {{0, A}, {230400, B}}.
224 std::map<int, ParameterSet> settings_by_resolution;
225 };
226 // Performance flags, ordered by |min_pixel_count|.
227 const PerformanceFlags performance_flags_;
228 // Caching of of |speed_configs_|, where index i maps to the resolution as
229 // specified in |codec_.spatialLayer[i]|.
230 std::vector<PerformanceFlags::ParameterSet>
231 performance_flags_by_spatial_index_;
232 void UpdatePerformanceFlags();
233 static PerformanceFlags ParsePerformanceFlagsFromTrials(
234 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig& trials);
235 static PerformanceFlags GetDefaultPerformanceFlags();
236
237 int num_steady_state_frames_;
238 // Only set config when this flag is set.
239 bool config_changed_;
240
241 const LibvpxVp9EncoderInfoSettings encoder_info_override_;
242};
